D.q[5700] = "Sickos like you should be locked up.";
D.q[4372] = "Perfect! And thanks for taking such good care of me! Cheekah will surely want to thank me for taking such good care of her... well, anyway, we don\'t have time to think about that. Take these potions, they\'ll heal your wounds. I think you\'ve earned a bit of healing, don\'t you...";
D.q[2999] = "Just find a Purple Piwi... there are heaps in this area and at the entrance of the mine. Attack it gently without scaring it and you\'ll probably get a purple feather. If you don\'t get one, just try again. You\'ll surely get one sooner or later! You\'ll see what you\'ve won at the end of the fight. The items will be listed in your inventory...";
D.q[2631] = "In the end, how much are you ready to put in for my son?";
D.q[4149] = "Well, it\'s pretty easy. I must provide the creatures we breed on this island with flours made from cereals. We give them the best flours to capture and study in our labs and paddocks. But, they\'re becoming more and more hard to please and the flours that we used to give them no longer suit them!";
D.q[4447] = "Since you seem to be having trouble coming up with anything, your target is a mercenary employed by Bonta for strategic research. You\'ll find him in the Bonta library. Ok, off you go!";
D.q[3576] = "Money is the least of your worries. You\'ll be paid alright. Do a good job and you\'ll be paid. ";
D.q[4180] = "You haven\'t finished exterminating the creatures I asked you to! Hurry up!";
D.q[4987] = "So Danathor wants to launch a counter-attack.\nI don\'t thind that the moment is right, because the troops are not sufficiently equipped yet. If we attack now, we risk losing a lot of soldiers.";
D.q[1437] = "Snappers are a fairly weird species, you know, they come in all different sizes and fishermen come from all around to have a go at catching them. They always said the same thing about my fish, something about competitions or... I don\'t know. Anyway, I never understood them very well, but still, I decided to nickname my new fish the Contest Snapper.";
D.q[1523] = "So be it.\nBring this letter to Oto Mustam, and carry on your way.";
D.q[4669] = "So Gomery Mont was talking about you. Don\'t worry, he saw you were badly off and, not wanting to embarrass you, he came here on his own initiative. Without your help, he\'d still be stuck at the bottom of a skeleton-filled hole. You did your work, and I won\'t forget to tell Amayiro about it.";
D.q[2007] = "So I\'ve to make you a bow, huh? Did you bring the bow and the wool?";
D.q[2435] = "He must be hunting in the forest.";
D.q[3002] = "You didn\'t find any feathers? You know, you can find feathers on of winged creatures. Besides, these winged creatures can also fly and if you\'re talented enough you\'ll be able to read the future in them. Anyway! Just find a Purple Piwi... there are heaps in this area. Attack it and you\'ll probably get a purple feather. If you don\'t get any, just try again. You\'ll surely get one sooner or later! You can see what you won when fighting at the end of the fight. The items will be listed in your inventory...";
D.q[4258] = "So did you find what I asked you for?";
D.q[6291] = "So have you decided to give me back the jewels or would you rather end up in a meat slicer?";
D.q[5344] = "So do you have everything I need?";
D.q[4890] = "So did you get what I asked for?";
D.q[2443] = "However, there\'s something you need to know : if you happen to offend one of them by mistake, she\'ll probably be angry with you... Nothing serious, really, but she may want to stuff herself with your guts! She might wish to crush your bones as well! So, listen carefully...";
D.q[6432] = "I\'ve tried to remember, but I just can\'t think of anything else. Ahhh, yes. Wait. They spoke about meeting in camp ground to the west of... somewhere... as soon as they\'d finished what they were doing.";
D.q[4278] = "So it\'s who\'s looking for information on Xephires. I think I can help you there, but you\'ll have to do something for me first. And don\'t worry, it\'s nothing too big, it\'s hardly anything at all!";
D.q[2928] = "May the holy whirlwind come to you, give you the divine dexterity and send you flying with swiftness!";
D.q[6727] = "So it\'s you who\'s been slaughtering my men? We\'re going to put an end to your nasty Bontarian business.";
D.q[2934] = "May the holy flora root its strength within you and may its divine sap course through your veins!";
D.q[1564] = "Listen to me, adventurer, don\'t tell my wife I\'m here!";
D.q[3513] = "So now for the fresh products: Bworkcelhain\'s heart, Vampire brains, an eye of the Kaniger and Mushd mud. Don\'t forget to use the scalpel!";
D.q[3664] = "So talk to Xelorat Masket... I never understood that stuff.";
D.q[6125] = "So what about those souls I asked you for?";
D.q[6124] = "So what about those souls I asked you for?";
D.q[6123] = "So what about those souls I asked you for?";
D.q[6152] = "So what about those souls I asked you for?";
D.q[6150] = "So what about those souls I asked you for?";
D.q[6145] = "So what about those souls I asked you for?";
D.q[6140] = "So what about those souls I asked you for?";
D.q[2479] = "If I only knew! He was last seen taking the road to Amakna, since then nothing...";
D.q[6139] = "So what about those souls I asked you for?";
D.q[6138] = "So what about those souls I asked you for?";
D.q[6132] = "So what about those souls I asked you for?";
D.q[6130] = "So what about those souls I asked you for?";
D.q[6129] = "So what about those souls I asked you for?";
D.q[6128] = "So what about those souls I asked you for?";
D.q[6127] = "So what about those souls I asked you for?";
D.q[6126] = "So what about those souls I asked you for?";
D.q[6147] = "So what about those souls I asked you for?";
D.q[6155] = "So what about those souls I asked you for?";
D.q[5553] = "So what are you doing here!? Stop watching the grass grow and find a solution to all this!";
D.q[1479] = "So what? Go and get another staff and find a Bontarian who stinks of death!";
D.q[6114] = "Well, you are motivated, that\'s for sure. You are loyal to Bonta, and you proved that by taking risks for your Order. I am proud to welcome you into the ranks of the Legenday Heroines. All the same, the Tower of Gisgoul is still standing despite the Grande Fée d\'Artifice Hille, but that\'s another story.";
D.q[4267] = "So you just think that a Bontarian bigwig could just come and work for us? Well, the timing is right... I\'ve been thinking about that a lot lately. All the same, I hope for your sake that this Xephires is really the one who signed this document. People will talk otherwise.";
D.q[6186] = "So you rat-louse, you\'re here to see your idol?";
D.q[1199] = "So you want to stay under my tutelage, within the Order of the Valiant Heart. A wise choice you shouldn\'t regret. However, to validate your subscription, you\'ll have to find the clerk of the order. He scours the taverns since his cat pet died. Bring him here and we\'ll confirm your request.";
D.q[4159] = "So, do you want to go back to the island?";
D.q[3590] = "So you think you\'re a good farmer? Really? We\'ll see about that. We need lots and lots of grain - many mouths to feed, you know. It\'s good for business, but I need some extra hands. Go reap a few acres of wheat.";
D.q[2529] = "Is this for a libation to the goddess?";
D.q[3052] = "So, bunch of cons, you feel like rebelling? You didn\'t expect me to be back that quickly, did you? I can only think of one word to describe such a vile, despicable and mean attitude: Gwahahaha!";
D.q[2266] = "So, did you manage to get some decent scissors?";
D.q[4697] = "So, did you find anything suspicious?";
D.q[2392] = "So, mercenary, you\'re looking for animals to hunt and Kamas to spend? Well it\'s your lucky day! Have a look at the wanted posters, and bring back whoever you can.";
D.q[5043] = "So, did you visit the mines of Amakna?";
D.q[3831] = "So, ready for the adventure of a lifetime?";
D.q[3843] = "So, ready for the adventure of a lifetime?";
D.q[3837] = "So, ready for the adventure of a lifetime?";
D.q[3836] = "So, ready for the adventure of a lifetime?";
D.q[3835] = "So, ready for the adventure of a lifetime?";
D.q[3834] = "So, ready for the adventure of a lifetime?";
D.q[3833] = "So, ready for the adventure of a lifetime?";
D.q[3842] = "So, ready for the adventure of a lifetime?";
D.q[3841] = "So, ready for the adventure of a lifetime?";
D.q[3840] = "So, ready for the adventure of a lifetime?";
D.q[3839] = "So, ready for the adventure of a lifetime?";
D.q[4400] = "So, that peach?";
D.q[5203] = "So, this is the famous Ronan. I had imagined a... bigger man. We\'ll take care of it right away...\nAh, we\'ll have to go ask Raaga too. I need to learn some new techniques for brain washing... I think the Goblin should have a few. I think Raaga is in the library.";
D.q[3962] = "So, this Rasputin cake?";
D.q[2545] = "So, the old wise told you about this old legend... and you believed him?! Even among the Lenald people, there are very few who still believe in this story...But wise Lenald is absolutely convinced. Long long ago, the story goes, the Lenalds used to protect dragon eggs... It was such a long time ago...";
D.q[2577] = "My hats are gorgeous, absolutely gorgeous! My Pandawa headgear\'s almost brand new! Come closer! There won\'t be enough for everyone!";
D.q[3051] = "So, you bunch of cons feel like rebelling? You probably didn\'t think I\'d be back that early! Rahaaayaa!";
D.q[6006] = "So, you fresh-water seaman, what brings you here?";
D.q[2117] = "So, what about this delivery? Are you making headway?";
D.q[2251] = "So, you got it all? What about my four, poor Gobball legs... oh and the two lemons?";
D.q[3255] = "So, you wanna to go back awready?";
D.q[1201] = "So, you wish to continue under my supervision within the Order of the Salvatory Spirit. A clever choice that you won\'t regret. However, to finalise your membership, you\'ll need to find the clerk of the order. Since both her brothers have qualms, she\'s going from tavern to tavern to find them. Bring her back here and we\'ll confirm your request.";
D.q[2116] = "So, you think you can touch me now? Come on, HIT ME!";
D.q[4155] = "So? Did you find my sweet wabbit? How is he doing?";
D.q[4328] = "So? Did you find a way to pass on the message?";
D.q[3512] = "So?";
D.q[3972] = "Whaaat? Killed Wabbit? No inter, inter, no funny for big Bwork like me.";
D.q[4185] = "So? Did those Pirates bite the dust?";
D.q[2129] = "So, you think the Bearman\'s power is nearly gone?";
D.q[3864] = "So, you\'ve come here to check if everything\'s going well in the Castle... Don\'t worry, I watch over the throne!";
D.q[4866] = "Whaaat? What is that? You think I\'m going to drink that just because some stranger asked me?";
D.q[3089] = "I don\'t need this to please my King. My mere presence is enough to delight him. Find someone else who doesn\'t have my feline charisma.";
D.q[3386] = "Some nice fightin\' young \'un... I mus\' say! I got nothin\' else for ya. Go\' luck!";
D.q[2606] = "Very well! Come back if you find anything.... So long!";
D.q[2666] = "Some innocent people are in danger at the cemetery. I, Nergal, servant of Iop, widows and orphans, beg you to give me a teleportation rune to take me there as quickly as possible!";
D.q[5852] = "Some soft water fishermen were beaten up by crabs, which are normally very placid creatures. It must be those informers unless one of the King\'s cooks was attacked in the kitchen.";
D.q[327] = "Some of those who set out will never come back. And even those who do return, will be haunted for life. If you all happen to come back, I won\'t get over it myself. So no matter what happens, there\'s always a loser.";
D.q[4116] = "What gender is the person who\'s neither your brother nor your sister but still is your parents\' child?";
D.q[5742] = "What are you doing here? Shouldn\'t you be guarding the Statuette before the Bontarians arrive?";
D.q[2894] = "What are you doing here? Take the key and run away.";
D.q[6206] = "Someone called X? Hmm, yes, maybe I know something about it, but I don\'t usually talk about customers. They know that they can come here in full discretion.";
D.q[3746] = "Some wise harvesters don\'t actually sell all they gather. They keep some until they learn a second profession and save a few Kamas in the process.";
D.q[5235] = "Something else for your service?";
D.q[3105] = "I only miss my beloved. A soft purring pet should do for now. I want a white Bow Meow, as white as I am. Find me 6 so I can choose the whitest.";
D.q[3515] = "Something is missing, it\'s a little bit delicate but I think it\'s necessary, if not vital.";
D.q[3673] = "Soon you\'ll be fighting against the diabolical hordes of the evil Rushu. He mustn\'t become the thirteenth god, if he does, the apocalypse will surely come!";
D.q[300] = "Sometimes...";
D.q[2115] = "Sorry but I don\'t have time to talk with you. I\'ve got a lot of creatures to kill... Do you want me to show you what I\'m up to?";
D.q[2080] = "Sorry but I\'m a very busy Cra. I don\'t have time to make your acquaintance.";
D.q[6313] = "Sorry fella, but I\'m not drunk enough for that yet. *Hic*. Go have a look around Eltneg Wood. I\'m sure you\'ll find a troll there who\'ll satisfy you.";
D.q[2821] = "Sorry, I can\'t sell the hard stuff to tourists like you.";
D.q[3463] = "I need this recipe to open my brewery. Look harder.";
D.q[756] = "Do you remember the prisoner you delivered?\nHe\'s back on his feet and wants to slay skeletons with you!";
D.q[1626] = "Sorry, but I never talk to strangers...";
D.q[1874] = "Sorry, I don\'t have time to chat. My father\'s counting on me to take care of his herd of Gobballs. Says it\'s to help me grow up big and strong. Oh listen... one of them\'s bleating... see ya!";
D.q[301] = "Sorry, but my mission is to prevent young crazies like you from being gored to kingdom come in the blink of an eye. Don\'t hesitate to come back once you\'ve practised a little. Here, take your items back.";
D.q[2111] = "Sorry, kid. I\'m too busy right now...";
D.q[1608] = "Sorry, you don\'t have enough Kamas.";
D.q[1932] = "Sorry, but we don\'t give credit anymore.";
D.q[164] = "Sorry, but you lost. You might be luckier next time, don\'t hesitate to try your luck again.";
D.q[2718] = "The goddess Pandawa always keeps an eye on her glass, AND an eye on you... Remember it!";
D.q[1750] = "Srams are very nimble and strong characters, they try to find equipment that can increase their agility and strength.";
D.q[2698] = "Sshh! Listen... Can you hear that? Our goddess is thanking you through my words - this Dofus is quite a good copy! Grandapan admires these precious Dofus... Ask Grandapan anything you like...";
D.q[5487] = "If you like flowers, go and talk to Erty. He\'s a skilled botanist.";
D.q[4473] = "Start by searching in the smith and mining workshops. Not the Bontarian ones, mind you... or the ones around here.";
D.q[6738] = "Still no bandits in sight? I almost wish something dangerous would happen. How about you play the jester and make me laugh? No? Well, whatever...";
D.q[2022] = "Stop staring at me like that! Come on hit ME! Hit me hard, COME ON!";
D.q[3644] = "Stop wasting my time chatting. He\'s just here.";
D.q[4574] = "Threaten me you dare? Attack me you can, but your safety ensure I can\'t as a long time I\'ve not eaten for.";
D.q[3929] = "Strange things happening at the castle? Not really. I\'ve just seen Allisteria stopping by lately.";
D.q[3930] = "Strange things at the castle? Not really. We just had a visit from Allisteria. She\'s all grown-up now, she could be getting married soon!";
D.q[2153] = "No blood? You haven\'t found Radlu Minite, the Dark Miner? I\'m told that he spends most of his time tasting the Innkeeper\'s brandy. Come back to see me with a few drops of his blood.";
D.q[3926] = "Strange things happening at the castle? Not really. We just had a visit from Allisteria. Usually, she never leaves her Gobballs alone.";
D.q[2537] = "Surivitna\'s assistant is going to take you there. He\'s been asked to thank the goddess for her kindness. Our goddess can be VERY sensitive, you know... Even Grandapan doesn\'t forget to thank her in his prayers and that\'s really saying something!";
D.q[4386] = "No attack? Well there\'s no doubt about it. Someone high in the ranks is giving the bandits information, I\'m sure of it. They\'re probably bribing him to slow down investigations, too. That would explain why the council won\'t just go ahead and take the bandits down once and for all.";
D.q[2779] = "Huh?";
D.q[2780] = "As soon as you finish your training, come see me. I\'ll wait for you outside the Dojo.";
D.q[2429] = "Tailors are the movers and shakers in the world of fashion. Don\'t take them for a bunch of sissies though, their cloaks and hats can lend fearsome powers to those who wear them. It\'ll take a while to find your own style, but keep working at it and you\'ll soon have as many secrets to jealously guard as the unhelpful masters of your art. ";
D.q[2230] = "Well look at this! You\'re laaaayyyyte. I break out all over if my food isn\'t fresh... you think I\'m going to pay full price?";
D.q[3530] = "Take Kamas, I fill it with troofle and cook in the Fattrool. Then gobble it up and clean my greasy lips with this cloak.";
D.q[6454] = "Take that *BIFF!*\nWow, you look like you\'re enjoying it!";
D.q[1229] = "Take this pair of pliers! Extracting a Gobball tooth couldn\'t be easier! You put one foot on the beast, you choose a tooth and you yank!";
D.q[480] = "Take this, I\'ve written the list of messages that need to be sent on this parchment. Don\'t hesitate to come and talk to me should you need more information.";
D.q[2794] = "Don\'t say a word! I can feel death hanging around you... You want to enter the darkness of the forbidden forest, don\'t you?";
D.q[6408] = "I know nothing about it, I never cooked before I was captured by Brakmar. You\'d be better off asking Boud Chair, at the butchers\' workshop.";
D.q[2809] = "Another question, who wrote the book Pandawushu Art ?";
D.q[2813] = "A Gobbly is white with a black tail whereas a Pandawa is black with.... bamboos on his back! The path to illumination is a very long one! One day, little Scaraleaf, one day...";
D.q[3733] = "What\'s your poison?";
D.q[570] = "People say this island was created by the god Moon. In order to watch over it, he transformed himself into a creature of flesh and blood. No one but his worshippers can approach him, unless you make an offering. Put simply, if you want to pay Moon a visit, you\'ll need a lot of Kokonuts. Each time you pass a Koko totem, the number of Kokonuts equal to its height will automatically be removed from your inventory. Simple isn\'t it? Ohoh!";
D.q[2352] = "Tell me, you really want to become an alchemist ? Yes, I\'m a trainer. Well, so listen to me: a good alchemist must learn to understand the intensity, the magic essence, of every object and be able to manipulate it at will. Take a new look at every object that you possess now or that you have possessed in the past.";
D.q[2848] = "Excellent! You\'re now a Sankwa!";
D.q[2235] = "Thank for beautiful cake. It\'s for Oz. With that, he can do what I want him... Deliver on the time! Good!";
D.q[3684] = "Tell that good-for-nothing clown Qwizitor that there are heaps of parasites in the fields... they\'re destroying my crops. I\'m sure the lazy fool knows about it.";
D.q[3083] = "Thank you for being so... quiet about all this. If you\'ve got some spare time, come back to me. I might have a delivery for you.";
D.q[3102] = "Thank you so much for helping such a poor courtesan as I. I\'d love to live in a nice little house far away from the court. Bhen Neddal told me about his old hideout. Please go ask him if I can live there.";
D.q[1185] = "As I was saying, nothing could be eas... Ahem... Good luck with the trade. Oh, don\'t forget to find a good fish chopper, it\'s essential to your profession. Did I mention I sell them?";
D.q[2119] = "Thank you very much, come back soon if you want. You\'re a good worker!";
D.q[1322] = "Thank you so much, I can finish preparing the meal.";
D.q[1988] = "Thank you very much. \n*Yol turns to Locette and makes her drink the potion*";
D.q[1897] = "Thank you very much. I\'d better hurry! I don\'t have much time left before my first date. So, let\'s see now...";
D.q[2720] = "We\'re telling you, these paths are winding and the creatures that haunt this forest are not very friendly. But a certain Wally Elconom managed to draw a map of it. It could be useful for you to meet him. He\'s often seen round Amakna.";
D.q[2922] = "How come one of my apprentices is visiting me?";
D.q[6756] = "Let me remind you that it\'s you who\'ll have to dress up as a boy scout. That\'s what you\'re paid for after all.... Oh really, they don\'t pay you? Not at all?! Hmm, I think they\'re taking the pi... taking you... ehh... very far. You\'re an honest person, loyal to your city and generous. Well done.";
D.q[3311] = "Thank you! Our good King Allister will be able to parade on these first-class mounts!";
D.q[2257] = "Hey, thanks for the training, it was great! Just one problem though... with all that jumping around, some of our Gobballs escaped. No! Some went to the underpasses...";
D.q[294] = "I\'ll give you a Curryless Curry Bread if you give me 5 Evil Dandelion Flowers. I need them to mask the smell of old bread.";
D.q[2938] = "Congratulations! You defeated my henchmen and I. Please take this present by way of gratitude.";
D.q[2949] = "Hum";
D.q[1914] = "Let me explain: I need someone who\'s strong enough to haul 1500 bread pods and who can run fast - in short I need strength and nimbleness in equal measure... Look for someone who seems to fit the bill and have a chat... see if they know which side of their bread is buttered, know what I mean. Then fill in this form, get the candidate to put their palm on it and you\'ll know straight away if your choice is good...";
D.q[2945] = "I think you shouldn\'t be around here.";
D.q[5573] = "Greetings. Have you used the potion on the imposters\' bodies?";
D.q[3431] = "Thank you, thank you so much. could you go and talk to my wife, Mrs El?";
D.q[3098] = "Thank you. I\'m ready to face the shark now!";
D.q[3903] = "I\'m going to double the security... Since you warned me, I\'m hiring you. If you come back later, I should have work for you to do.";
D.q[2963] = "<B> test </B>\n<I>test </I>\n<U>test </U>";
D.q[3054] = "Thank you. Take this.";
D.q[5667] = "Thank you. When you\'ve finished with the rest, we\'ll leave for the ritual chamber.";
D.q[2966] = "So you\'re back? But you didn\'t bring back the Tofu eggs? But what on earth are you waiting for?";
D.q[3049] = "Warning! Only ghost pets can enter this cemetery #1!\nIf you have this kind of creature travelling with you, you can try to make it go in, but beware, it probably won\'t survive on its own. Other ghost pets should go with it, if it wants to get back out of this cemetery.\nIf your ghost pet defeats Oshima\'s, it will most likely get to meet him.\n\nAre you sure you want to make one of your ghost pets go into this cemetery?";
D.q[2967] = "Hello Hello adventurer. What can I do for you?";
D.q[2979] = "Can\'t wait for the flood!";
D.q[3121] = "You beat me... But I really appreciated... this fight... It was great... \nThe way you sway your hips... such style... just incredible...\nYou\'re way too... fast... for me...\nYou really have... a special... fighting... \nYou\'re a bit of an eccentric... just like me...\nI hope... that... you have a good... life...";
D.q[915] = "Thanks #1! You\'re so helpful. I\'ll now be able to train my guys properly.";
D.q[1906] = "Thanks a lot! Here is the list of people who need deliveries. They must receive their cakes within... 20 minutes. The cakes have already been paid for but you must collect the delivery charges. You can keep the money too.";
D.q[1119] = "Thanks a lot! With these flowers my Tabi should regain strength.";
D.q[2569] = "Thanks a lot! Prayers go up faster when they\'re washed down with a good glass of Pandneken! You can go for a walk while I finish my Pandn... prayer.";
D.q[6334] = "Thanks a lot, but I\'d rather you kept the money. It\'s a pleasure to give a fresh-faced beauty like you a copy of the Canine Training Technique.";
D.q[1258] = "Thanks a lot, hehehe, gotcha! How would a little girl like me possibly know the recipe for a magic poison?! Hahaha!";
D.q[1920] = "Thanks a lot. Go see the innkeeper, Tek Abir, he must be getting used to it by now!";
D.q[1855] = "Thanks a lot. Here\'s some pocket money for you, you deserve it. I wonder what these Mimice are doing round here. It must be down to all this mess in the underpasses. It pushes the Mimice above ground... TwitTwit agrees with me too!";
D.q[4147] = "Thanks a lot. I now have everything I need.";
D.q[6465] = "Thanks a lot. I sure owe you one. I\'ll give you some of the synthetic jelly that I invented myself... and the recipe so you can make more. If you\'re not skilled enough to do it, just ask a handyman to help you out. Let me tell you right now though, that\'s the last bit of jelly you get off me so just make sure that the handyman who helps you doesn\'t mess things up!";
D.q[1924] = "Thanks a lot. Take this, it\'s a sample of what we can do, don\'t hesitate to come back. Oh, and since you\'re here, would you be interested in making some easy money? I need other materials.";
D.q[2997] = "So? You still haven\'t found a copy of my book? Go and look in Astrub, you should be able to find one there!";
D.q[5526] = "Thanks a lot. You just got me a biiig bonus, kid.";
D.q[2031] = "You\'re quite fast, that\'s a good thing. But what\'s even more important is the strength you invest in your attacks and an unfailing courage to defend your convictions till the end. Above all, you must be just. At all times... Remember these things I tell you now, young one. Now, give me your sword and I\'ll affix the mark that will seal your fate... *Rok uses various tools but doesn\'t appear to be good with his hands*... Here you go, finished!";
D.q[1219] = "Thanks and welcome, Bro!";
D.q[4436] = "Thanks again.";
D.q[2846] = "Let the sun shine, let the sun shine in, the suuuunnn shine iiiiinnnnn...... Pardon me? I\'m busy. I can\'t help you right now.";
D.q[3012] = "Go and see Hugo Bello, in the Temple of the goddess Feca. He\'ll be able to get you some.";
D.q[3205] = "It\'s very easy! You need a key to enter! I used to be the only one to have the key, but things changed. I think I lost my bunch of keys on this island, but I don\'t know where. One of these damned creatures probably stole it from me when I was sleeping.";
D.q[3709] = "Thanks for the advice. You look like a veteran already. I\'m going to sleep for a while... My god Sadida always says that you gotta rest if you\'ve been thinking too much.";
D.q[2254] = "Thanks for the legs... But I still need the 2 lemons... Come on! I\'m starving...";
D.q[5188] = "Thanks for proving my innocence, I will be forever in your debt.";
D.q[3111] = "Thanks for the shovel. Please go thank Rocco Fidelio for his bags of potatoes. Tell him that they should arrest some more people and put some life into this wonderful jail by the water. Why don\'t you stay with me and peel some potatoes. It\'s quite an art, you know!";
D.q[1024] = "Thanks for the powder! Brakmarians had better watch out! Heh heh heh!";
D.q[2141] = "Did you get your answer? Now give it to Joe... bloody penny-pincher.";
D.q[584] = "Thanks meat. Can go village. You visit and come back here be cooked! You not go far!";
D.q[2126] = "Thanks kid, you\'ll always be welcome in here. If you ever need some dough, we\'ll always have some work for you.";
D.q[1104] = "Oh, putrid air, constant dark, shadow stains on the wall... How beautiful that sad old city of Brakmar is!";
D.q[5256] = "I\'ve got a finger in that particular pie, come back and see me later.";
D.q[4167] = "Thanks to you, I feel alive and want to seduce Marguerite again... I never enjoyed seduction so much!";
D.q[1064] = "Thanks sonny. You\'ve done some good work, it\'s true. But you\'ll need to do more than that to stand among the great in Brakmar.";
D.q[920] = "Thanks sonny, that was fast! You seem to be spritely and well-disciplined...";
D.q[3039] = "Here. Take this book. Read it when you\'ve completed your mission! Keep your eyes wide open!";
D.q[6169] = "Stop there. I watch over this city so no funny business or it\'s straight to prison without passing go, capisci?";
D.q[1337] = "Thanks to you, we can attend the ceremony. Well, it\'s time for a snooze until this evening.";
D.q[2068] = "Thanks to you. Ah, I\'ve forgotten to tell you. If she starts running, don\'t let her out of your sight. I want you to be stuck to her like a leech. That way, I\'m sure she won\'t do something stupid. Well I think everything will be alright...I leave her in your care. See you.";
D.q[3070] = "Eating with that clumsy old Site Chief? You\'re not the first messenger he\'s sent me... When he comes for himself, well, we\'ll see!";
D.q[2097] = "Thanks, I knew I could count on you.";
D.q[6238] = "Thanks, I didn\'t know Brakmarians could be so nice. This document must be very important I suppose. What exactly do you want from Xephires? It\'s strange all the same that the Brakmarians would be so interested in a Bontarian.";
D.q[3485] = "Thanks, it\'s because I ate too many Red Goblins during the Battle of Bworkdrift. I was on the White Goblins side.";
D.q[3081] = "Is that old Wartella making trouble for me? HA! It\'s not for nothing she\'s the customs officer. I tell you, the life of a smuggler isn\'t as easy as it used to be. Come back to me and I\'ll give you some contraband in return. And be quick or I\'ll find you and feed you to the real sharks!";
D.q[2749] = "I can see in your eyes you want to go to the evil forest, am I right?";
D.q[1427] = "Thanks, here are 200 Kamas for the errand. Don\'t hesitate to come back again, I regularly need ingredients.";
D.q[4886] = "If Amayiro is plotting against Brakmar, I\'d be honoured to help.";
D.q[4814] = "Thanks. If Oto becomes any more crazy than he is now, I wouldn\'t even want to think about the repercussions for Brakmar, and the rest of the world.";
D.q[1282] = "Thanks. I\'ll quietly study it. I hope you enjoyed your stroll because your next missions won\'t be quite as peaceful.";
D.q[1622] = "Get out of my way! I lost the electro-inductor for my Bumper and I can\'t go home. If only I had enough oclitic energy to fix my BZ4A model...";
D.q[579] = "That would be rrreeeeeally cute *hic* Without himmmm my geenniuss was silenced *hic* But I need a commpleette one *hic* My trrreasure will then beecome mmy due *hic*";
D.q[1055] = "That buffoon? Well, what a stroke of luck for him. Anyway, this time I\'m not grateful for your services. You have my permission to do whatever you like. I don\'t have time to take care of you at the moment, so clear off!";
D.q[5623] = "That would have been quick, don\'t you think? You did very well, so I\'m going to give you the title of Follower of Writing.\nMay Jiva watch over you.";
D.q[3107] = "How slow can you be? My other little servants would have finished this job long ago!";
D.q[2788] = "I roughly know my way to get to the guard at the back of the room. I can hear him snore as usual. Just quietly observe the room from here. If you see I can move a little without being seen, hit the ground once. Guards here are quite organised. If you observe them well you should be able to guide me easily. The fat one at the back of the room sleeps heavily. Use his snores to tell me when I can safely jump on him. If you understood, we\'ll give it a go.";
D.q[4015] = "That\'s a decent amount, I\'ll follow you. Do you have an outfit for me?";
D.q[6359] = "That\'s a Bontarian warship, that, no? I didn\'t have a clue they were on the way. You should go and question Wartella, she should have up-to-date info on what Bontarians ships are on their way here, even if no one seems to be telling me.";
D.q[2188] = "So, the delivery man is safe? Not yet? Hang in there, you can do it.";
D.q[4891] = "(Abruptly, everything goes black and you fall to the floor. Attacking Elturt wasn\'t such a good idea after all.)";
D.q[2474] = "That\'s a fine bridge alright! We gave the Pandawas quite a hand! But we must fill in these breaches or else everything might just collapse. Yep... amber... that\'s what we need.";
D.q[6566] = "That\'s a good little doggy. Now pick your nose with your thumbs.";
D.q[6431] = "We\'ve been having problems with a bunch of tipsy Ecaflips. The situation has gotten so bad that we\'ve almost had to use physical force. Their leader finally told them off, saying that they had a job to do and that they were meant to do it discreetly.";
D.q[634] = "Forgetfulness of Wild grasses: 5 vervains, 10 elm wood, 40 evil dandelion stems, 40 irons, 40 treechnid roots.\nExpiation Arrow: 5 flexible woods, 5 ultra-powerful bows of the king of the Borins, 1 whetstone, 10 bloods of vampire, 10 leather panties of Captain Chafer.\nForgetfulness of Preventive Word: 3 small bells, 50 smoothers, 50 farters\nForgetfulness of Attraction: 4 stinging nettles, 10 celebrities, 10 rings of satisfaction, 2 salt \'n\' battery capes";
D.q[5843] = "That\'s a pile of nonsense. As if those statuettes could actually affect people. Actually, did you see the flowers I just had sent to me? I decided to change the decoration, it\'s too sullen and sinister. I need something bubbly... something gay.";
D.q[3161] = "Come here, come here, if you dare!";
D.q[3078] = "That\'s better. I\'m exhausted from all this excitement. Go get me some Piglet Milk and I\'ll give you a few candies. I don\'t want them anymore, they\'re bad for my teeth.";
D.q[5604] = "That\'s great news! Now that the cereals are growing quicker, we\'ll have plenty of food for the Dragoturkeys. We could even try the same technique for the cereals we feed the troops with. Well, congratulations, I pronounce you a Squire of the realm.";
D.q[2585] = "I\'m not trying to get money out of you, my good man, you\'ll need it! But before you put it on, smell it as you would a flower...";
D.q[2437] = "Everything to do with fishing is in the kralove-shaped building.";
D.q[3988] = "That\'s not impowtant to me! Let\'s find othew followews.";
D.q[307] = "No, that\'s not right!";
D.q[4653] = "Ah, excellent, you followed my orders well. So much for the spy, he should have been better at hiding!\nHere\'s your reward.";
D.q[4089] = "That\'s not so easy. Are you ready to try again?";
D.q[6329] = "That\'s shocking! You really have a heart of stone more solid than that of a Crackler!";
D.q[5854] = "That\'s very strange, and it doesn\'t bode well for us. I hate when a situation gets out of control I\'m going to find out more, and you go see Domen. He\'s looking for someone discreet for some important jobs.";
D.q[6767] = "That\'s what the Sadida used to tell me when we\'d talk... Well... I guess I did most of the talking, he used to listen, he was very interested, I can tell you. But talking doesn\'t solve the fact that you\'re still hanging around here. Do you want me to get you out of here?";
D.q[1188] = "The Order of the Sharp Eye is in charge of the missions within Bonta that require delicacy and tact. Some say we\'re spies and saboteurs but I\'d rather describe our job as dusting for information and doing some big time mopping-up from time to time...";
D.q[843] = "The Bontarians are unusually calm, I wonder what\'s going on. One of our spies has infiltrated Bonta, his name is Trojen Tihpor. He\'ll be on duty around the ramparts of the city right about now. Try to talk to him as discreetly as possible and come back to me to report any activity over there.";
D.q[842] = "The Bontarians have been pretty calm lately. Nothing\'s happening really. This is your chance to get some rest.";
D.q[1706] = "The Ecaflip temple is located northward of the village of Amakna. Talk to Felenie Grismina to begin your training.";
D.q[1709] = "The Cra temple is located southward of the village of Amakna. Talk to Eluhise Valing to begin your training.";
D.q[3357] = "The Royal Gobball is going down! OH YEAH!";
D.q[1641] = "The Feca temple is located eastward near the Asse coast. Talk to Hirpine Fecalamite to continue your training.";
D.q[1707] = "The Eniripsa temple is located eastward of the village of Amakna. Talk to Limine Bryone to begin your training.";
D.q[3744] = "An alchemist can create numerous potions which he stores in flasks. He can brew healing potions, recall potions (that will take you back to your last saved point), forgetfulness potions for professions and many other useful concoctions!";
D.q[1708] = "The Iop temple is located southward of the village of Amakna. Talk to Tajide Ragalde to begin your training.";
D.q[3312] = "The King is waiting for his stud farm. You\'ve been entrusted with a royal mission. Try to hurry up!";
D.q[3323] = "The Koalak Mountain was not very well mapped. I\'d like some young curious and courageous adventurers to bring me back a precise description of this far away region.";
D.q[2347] = "Alchemists manipulate elements, both magical and ordinary substances. We are the transformers of materials. Many believe that we are a bunch of pencil pushers, but it\'s not true. A real alchemist spends as much time running around the world in search of rare ingredients as in the lab. And I can tell you from experience that when our supply of Boowolf hair gets low, you need to have a taste for adventure to fill it up again!";
D.q[3522] = "The Outtahir spell!";
D.q[2380] = "It takes a long time to become a blacksmith and you need to know a lot of people. You can\'t be a blacksmith if you don\'t know a good miner and a good lumberjack to get the raw materials you need. Well, you could always go to the marketplace and pay for all this, but I\'m not too fond of that myself.";
D.q[3919] = "The Prince of Ooha? Yes, I believe he\'s gone hunting south of Bonta, but I don\'t know where exactly. Besides, I think he left alone, which seems quite strange for a prince.";
D.q[3918] = "The Prince of Wa? Yes, I believe he\'s gone hunting south of Bonta, but I don\'t know where exactly. Besides, I think he left alone, which seems quite strange for a prince.";
D.q[2751] = "The Shaman seems qualified to give you a certificate. Go see him.";
D.q[1710] = "The Sadida temple is located southward of the village of Amakna. Talk to Silimote Fougaris to begin your training.";
D.q[4236] = "Though it benefited from immunity for so long, the creature nourished a fierce hatred for its jailors, before breaking free. Nothing remains but scraps of fur. Who knows what chaos awaits the region.";
D.q[5376] = "They won\'t keep me prisoner for long. My Brakmarian brothers will set me free!";
D.q[1704] = "The Sram temple is located southwest from here. Talk to Sirmine Daguiero to begin your training.";
D.q[1187] = "The Valiant Heart groups together the most valourous warriors of Bonta. Bravery, will and determination are required to join it. Our motto could be :\'We must hit quick, must hit strong, that the Devil may never arise.\'";
D.q[6059] = "The are many causes for friction between Raval\'s Rogues and the members of the Order of the Valiant Heart. It seems that Raval is plotting against us. He must stop all activities immediately or run the risk of open warfare between the Rogues and our militia.";
D.q[3122] = "I\'ve been locked up... in my own cave... for ages...\nHow come?... How is this possible?\nI don\'t... know...\nIt\'s Skeunk... and his bloody Sadidettes... they stole... my precious... my Dofus... mine... the one I loved so much...\nHum... You\'re not the first to come here...\nOshar Marif... next to me... also tried to confront me... but... I defeated him... and he\'s too weak... to leave on his own...";
D.q[3612] = "The beautiful Pinkgob, Bworkcine\'s slave. Can you free her?";
D.q[2799] = "The call of the wild, even when it\'s cursed, turns you on... do you hear that, young disciple?";
D.q[3938] = "The castle is in a state of great agitation. You should ask Walt. He\'s bringing bags to them.";
D.q[1485] = "It\'s quite simple, you just have to find the entrance to the legendary cave of the golden larvae. According to legend, it\'s to be found just a little West of Amakna. The secret powers of your golden larva will allow you to enter freely.";
D.q[4770] = "The blade has been half forged, and now is the time to impregnate it with demonic power. Go and see Lagren Doowile down there, he\'ll tell you how to do it.";
D.q[1714] = "The challenge is easy. As you probably noticed, there are a lot of animals in the courtyard of this temple. There\'s a black Tofu among them. Bring me one of its black feathers to prove your worth.";
D.q[6728] = "The conflict between the two great cities loses its sparkle sometimes. It needs a little kick start, and I\'m here to help anyone who agrees with me. I\'ve a talent for finding people, let\'s say I\'m a tracker. Tempting, isn\'t it?!";
D.q[2015] = "Crystal phials of pale Anthir, hummm... you want to see the future? You seem a little inexperienced for that to me. Well, be very careful, may folk have caused permanent damage to their eyes with these crystals. Here you are.";
D.q[5575] = "Please be quiet! Your book is here... no... here... ah yes. Quiet, please. Ok, you have what you want, now scram!";
D.q[4327] = "The deal is done. He will get it.";
D.q[1135] = "Interesting. The time has come to destroy Bonta the Usurper. The latest information you brought me will enable us to improve our plan of action.";
D.q[2428] = "Using leather and sometimes metal, the shoemaker crafts the most beautiful belts and boots. If they\'re married with the right magical materials, belts can give the wearer terrifying powers.";
D.q[3408] = "Though you keep on going, the road seems to get longer and longer, is all this effort really worth it?";
D.q[3896] = "Good morning, faithful servant! Long live our beloved King! May he reign for many years!";
D.q[4418] = "The discovery of this traitor has left our superiors very suspicious indeed. I\'d rather not give you the job for the moment.";
D.q[962] = "The districts of Bonta are divided according to the different activities fulfilled by the craftsmen. You can easily recognize the main activity of a district thanks to the ornaments on the front of the houses and to the masts. The different coat of arms inscribe on the masts belong to the trade association.";
D.q[1983] = "The doctor doesn\'t recognize the disease, but he refuses to abandon her to her sad state. He asked me if he could try different remedies. I accepted, of course, but he lacks some ingredients, he can\'t come here and I can\'t bring myself to leave her. Would you help me?";
D.q[1373] = "Have you found the samples I asked for?";
D.q[4300] = "Did you get the materials I asked for or do I\'ve to find someone more competent to finish the task?";
D.q[331] = "You don\'t have everything I asked you for! Don\'t try to swindle me, or I\'ll call my friend Baracurt to kick your pants off! Heeeeeelp!";
D.q[4057] = "A Wabbit prince is better than nothing, with a bit of luck I should be able to make everyone happy. Let me study the preparations while you go get that prince and convince him to marry the princess.";
D.q[7466] = "If you use the first power, all of your characteristics will be reset to zero. You\'ll lose any points that you gained from characteristic scrolls but you\'ll get back everything else.";
D.q[2287] = "Just like you, all the creatures down here are either resistant or sensitive to the four essential elements - air, earth, fire, water. Learn how to recognize their strengths and weaknesses (as well as yours) and the World will be safe for you. Or almost.";
D.q[3751] = "The first thing you must do is load the materials into the tool you\'re using. Then, grind your wheat with the crusher. Two measures of wheat to one measure of flour should be fine. You should see the result of your work before you combine anything.";
D.q[7066] = "The following stones...";
D.q[1672] = "ROLL UP ROLL UP! TEST YOUR MEMORY! REVEAL YOUR HIDDEN POWER! You! Yes, you there! I can feel your great inner strength-bucket! Do you want to tip it over for the world to see? It\'s only 20 Kamas and you stand to win a lot of Trool Tokens.";
D.q[1470] = "(What are you doing here, it\'s no place for a demon like you... Plus, you\'ll blow my cover, go on, off you go or I\'ll call the guard.)";
D.q[2719] = "The goddess did well to guide your steps towards this Dojo. I\'m going to teach you the sublime art that we call Pandawushu... The fee is 10,000 Kamas, payable in advance...";
D.q[4211] = "Ahem, according to your constitution, I can tell that I\'ll need a Great Coralator relic, a Gourlo the Terrible relic and a Greater Bherb relic to prepare your potion. Once ground to powder, I\'ll be able to withdraw all the magic power I need from them.";
D.q[136] = "(Grizmine writes your name down on a card, throws several 37-faced dice up in the air, catches them, makes some strange calculations, scratches his whiskers and thinks...)";
D.q[2233] = "Great! Come back in 5 minutes. I\'m going to make you a great bow...";
D.q[4729] = "The hilt of the sword is made of wood, but not just any old wood. Hornbeam Wood bewitched by dark magic is needed, but I don\'t know how to do all this.\nSearch the lumberjacks\' workshops and find somone who does.";
D.q[3184] = "Last time I saw Lord Crow, he was in the first room of the library, or maybe in the second one, or was it in the fifth? or the sixth?... Well, I don\'t remember.";
D.q[1884] = "This information is interesting, very interesting. Still, I need to know more to make up my mind. There\'s a guy in Amakna, a certain Three-Flower... he knows about the plants and trees. Ask him to show you round the region. When you\'re done, write a report and bring it to me when you come back to Astrub! Off you run, young disciple. Hihihiii!";
D.q[825] = "Ask the guard at the door if he needs a hand, as I\'ve got nothing for you to do.";
D.q[3047] = "We can finally go back to Allister\'s sumptuous Castle.";
D.q[6729] = "Do you need anything?";
D.q[3185] = "Last time I saw Lord Crow, he was hiding in the first room, or maybe in the second one, or was it in the fifth? or the sixth?.... Well, I don\'t remember.";
D.q[3190] = "Last time I saw Lord Crow, he was hiding in the third room, or maybe in the fourth one, or was it in the seventh? or the eighth?.... Well, I don\'t remember.";
D.q[3187] = "Last time I saw Lord Crow, he was hiding in the third room, or maybe in the fourth one, or was it in the seventh? or the eighth?.... Well, I don\'t remember.";
D.q[3196] = "Last time I saw Lord Crow, he was hiding in the ninth room, or maybe in the tenth one, or was it in the thirteenth? or the fourteenth?... Well, I don\'t remember.";
D.q[3189] = "Last time I saw Lord Crow, he was hiding in the first room, or maybe in the second one, or was it in the fifth? or the sixth?.... Well, I don\'t remember.";
D.q[3186] = "Last time I saw Lord Crow, he was hiding in the third room, or maybe in the fourth one, or was it in the seventh? or the eighth?.... Well, I don\'t remember.";
D.q[3197] = "Last time I saw Lord Crow, he was hiding in the ninth room, or maybe in the tenth one, or was it in the thirteenth? or the fourteenth?... Well, I don\'t remember.";
D.q[3598] = "Lumberjack? Well, you need an expert eye and you must be willing to travel. Good trees are rare. Besides, you must preserve forests. A lot of craft industries are born from this profession. Yes really... Can you think of something that\'s not made out of wood? So, shall we start? ";
D.q[2285] = "The inhabitants of our land are very fascinating creatures. There\'s nothing like setting off to discover the local wildlife and improving your zoological and botanical knowledge. A light heart and good will, it\'s all you need to give them the willies most of the time.";
D.q[554] = "The island\'s inhabitants are quite surly at first sight, but don\'t think they have a grudge against you! It\'s usually the opposite, they love tourists. Nothing surpasses their pleasant company except being with the Chief himself. Some people say he\'s the embodiment of the God of the island: Moon. Don\'t rely too much on appearances, he\'s really smart and incredibly funny.";
D.q[571] = "The island\'s inhabitants? Hahaha! There are pirates wandering around the southern part of the jungle, but they aren\'t very friendly to strangers. Ohohoh. They were already there when I came here and they will probably still be there when you leave. I guess they must really like this island! Hahaha!";
D.q[2113] = "Bye! Come back when you\'re a bit less green!";
D.q[1652] = "The inhabitants of this village are very clever, but still haven\'t managed to make their village impregnable.\n*Polishes her crystal ball*\nBonta\'s troops control the village for the moment, but maybe not for long...";
D.q[2972] = "Haha! Typical! You\'ve been asked to do something and you\'ve done it! You really thought I\'d believe you? Well... A Pandawa, you say? It could be, though! Who could be that stupid to brag about a Dofawa?";
D.q[4004] = "Okay... but... the pay has to be good! I don\'t want to be a cook all my life.";
D.q[5146] = "Finally finished! I really thought I would die before the end of the trial because of the smell of rotten snapper coming from that Sram.";
D.q[5184] = "Proooo-teeect As\'Ruoy\'Dnim.";
D.q[368] = "We need 80 units of Blue Jelly and 30 units of Mint Jelly.";
D.q[4312] = "";
D.q[5032] = "Pick the symbol you want in the safes, I\'ll bring you out when it\'s done.";
D.q[4812] = "The last piece. Soon, it will be mine!";
D.q[1955] = "The lager has been delivered, thank you very much! You\'ve kept the thieves at bay for now but what about tomorrow? Will you be able to stop them again?";
D.q[173] = "The innkeeper asked me to bring him Hops for his brewer friends but I don\'t have time to go all the way over to see Farle Ingalsse, the Farmer. \nBring me a unit of hops from him and I\'ll give you a beer on the house.";
D.q[5694] = "The location that Terra Tibya gave us didn\'t have more than a few monsters and some of that dirty old incarnated powdered toenail. We\'ve been fooled... we look ridiculous now. It\'s unacceptable.\nGo back and interrogate Terra Bitya some more and make her tell you where the statuettes are.";
D.q[4340] = "The local wine merchant has disappeared. I suspect he has been kidnapped, but don\'t take my word for it. Could you go ask the Bagrutte Innkeeper if he knows anything about it? The merchant often used to pay him a visit.";
D.q[2260] = "The map and your geographical position will prove very useful to travel in the world. The most important places are pinpointed with different icons. You can also use them to pinpoint an important place to go with this blue flag. Your compass will then show you the way to that place.";
D.q[2432] = "The master is not at the sawmill right now, he\'s at the wood market.";
D.q[5720] = "The master of your Order told me he had a mission for you, so why are you still here?";
D.q[2433] = "The master\'s out of town, he went to the mine. You\'ll probably find him at the entrance of the mines north-east of here.";
D.q[4222] = "The mechanism we use to open this door is complex and secret. We don\'t want to spoil this creature by letting it devour stupid adventurers. \nNever forget that this creature is extremely powerful and dangerous, the dragon carcass that we found in the peat bog makes us believe that it\'s been killed by this creature.";
D.q[2466] = "Go talk to my brother Wilde instead. He explains things so clearly, he\'ll soon have you understanding things you didn\'t know existed.";
D.q[4847] = "The militiaman Kit Dingaround has been found guilty of serious treason against Bonta. He will serve a life sentence of hard labour in prison.";
D.q[4852] = "The militiaman Kit Dingaround has been found innocent of all charges of treason against Bonta. He is now free to return to his position as militiaman from tomorrow on.";
D.q[4228] = "This island has existed time out of mind, long before the creation of the Clock of Xelor or the formation of the continents! This monster is a living god, it cannot be defeated. I don\'t know if you\'re worthy to even contemplate what it means to confront him.";
D.q[4684] = "The moth-eaten equipment we\'ve given to our militians won\'t do much good. I found a very, very interesting book about a cursed tear in the library. But for the moment, Domien that uselss old so and so let me know that he wants to talk to you.";
D.q[1054] = "The name o\' tha\' killa for ya boss? Suuuurrrreeee I know it! Here, I w\'ot\' it on this paipa. Take it.";
D.q[4562] = "This item could give us the upper hand against the Brakmarians.";
D.q[6218] = "The only person I know whose name begins with an X and who has set foot in the Tower of Bonta is Xephires. I don\'t know any more than that, I\'ve just met him a few times in the Bagrutte Inn.";
D.q[3641] = "The newbie\'s making fun of me! I\'ll teach you! I can tell you that you\'ll obey. You\'ll spit blood and cry like the little girl you are!";
D.q[1288] = "The particular lighting and decor of this prison was inspired by Brakmar. I hope you enjoy your stay... ha-ha-ha!";
D.q[1898] = "The pebbles I picked up on the carpet undoubtedly come from the North-East cave. So let\'s go there together, we\'ll have double the luck, right. You go on ahead... I\'ve to deal with something back here. I\'ll join you, don\'t worry.";
D.q[1659] = "The prism of this area hasn\'t been rebuilt yet. The Dopple territory cannot be attacked for the moment.";
D.q[3742] = "The port of Madrestam is full of young fishermen. It\'s a nice spot for a bit of fishing.";
D.q[4269] = "I\'d prefer if you didn\'t go alone. We don\'t know how many bandits there are in the area or how well they\'re armed.";
D.q[4292] = "So? Did you two have a chat?";
D.q[5837] = "The protectors of the cities have decided to use the power of Statues of Sumens. Everyone thought they had the two real statuettes, which meant that the real real ones lost their power as soon as they were set free. The protectors then realiised that the statuette they stole from the city was itself only a common copy! The whole world will be upset by this, and you\'re going to go investigate.\n\nVisit the other order masters and find out their opinion. Then go see Oto Mustam to find out how all this has affected him. After you\'ve done all this, come and report to me.";
D.q[4343] = "Disappeared?! I don\'t believe it... he was one of my best clients!\nWell, after his trip here, he started going to his place, a little to the east of here.";
D.q[4380] = "So do you have the jewel?";
D.q[4363] = "I\'ve heard about a group of bandits who are wreaking havoc through the Cania Plains, not far from the fair. They may even have come as far as here...\nI want you to go investigate over there. Come back if you find something.";
D.q[1290] = "Welcome to the darkness of our Inn. Please have a seat.";
D.q[415] = "The province of Amakna is quiet. But sometimes, you\'ll have to fight monsters, to defend yourself against assailants or to challenge other people.";
D.q[3699] = "The quantities are perfect... the flasks are clean... and yet, this potion is not working like it should. I wonder if what I\'m doing is legal!";
D.q[3445] = "The recipe of the Filtounga? Why should I give you this book?";
D.q[5616] = "The renegades\' souls have returned to their bodies. You can go question them now. I want to know some of the things they told the Brakmarians. Jiva cannot bear such treachery.";
D.q[6721] = "The room is located under the Tower of Brakmar. You can get there through a little passageway between two shelves, in the south-west part of the tower, all the way at the bottom.";
D.q[5731] = "The second Statuette of Sumens mustn\'t stay in the hands of the Brakmarians. They won\'t hesitate for a second to use it for evil.";
D.q[6167] = "Hello, go see Otomai. He\'ll give you some work to do, according to your abilities. Maybe he\'ll even tell you a few of his secrets.";
D.q[4995] = "The scroll will permit you to take on the appearance of a Dreggon, so freeing you to go where you need to. It\'s a lot better than trying to rent a costume... plus this way, we don\'t need to put down a deposit!";
D.q[2655] = "The shield smith is sending you? Very well. Get your training shield and tell me when you\'re ready.";
D.q[6350] = "The smith refused to help so you popped him off? You did well. If we can\'t have that bloody smith, no one will. That\'s sooo... Brakmarian, don\'t you think!?\nI wanted to give you something to do once the smith was back in our camp, but that won\'t happen. Ah, you\'d better come back to see me later.";
D.q[2671] = "The state of the Enutrofs I\'m taking care of worries me. Most of them come from the Mines of Astrub. Go see Gasdaure, she\'s the one sending me all those sick people. If you want to help me... help her first!";
D.q[4448] = "The tactician is in the Bonta library. Watch out for Whitish Fang.";
D.q[3716] = "To restore your energy, you can also just sit down. Come back later, when you\'re strong enough to help me carry some buckets of water.";
D.q[1655] = "The territory of the Dopples, hmmm, it\'s a place overflowing with Magic. The creatures that live there can take on the appearance of anything they see.\n*Polishes her crystal ball*\nI can see frequent confusion in alignments there, for the moment\nBrakmar troops have taken control of the area.";
D.q[4135] = "The trip was actually rather short and rather quiet, I was easily able to deal with what little danger there was. I might be old but I\'ve still got it!";
D.q[2270] = "The underpasses are not safe lately. And the Tofus come back sick, it\'s weird...Some of us are on patrol to see what\'s going on in there.";
D.q[3238] = "The village you\'re in is none other than the old village of Amakna.\nIts inhabitants lived there peacefully for a very long time until these mysterious Dreggons turned up and devastated the village eating and burning up most of the inhabitants. Those who survived, took refuge in what we now call the Castle of Amakna.";
D.q[757] = "To show your devotion to the militia, you\'ll have to find two raw recruits. Give them these coupons and tell them to come see me to subscribe to the militia.";
D.q[611] = "Well done, a deal\'s a deal! Here are your shorts. See you again sometime...";
D.q[1510] = "The war between Bonta and Brakmar used to be of a divine nature, more precisely a war against the Protectors of the months. Brakmar was built to honour Rushu and to ensure his supremacy. The war reached its highest point and then the two cities disappeared all at once. Since then, no protector got himself talked about.";
D.q[4038] = "The wedding dress? Yes, it\'s ready but the veil isn\'t. The steward asked for an opaque one so that the bride can\'t see her future husband. But I haven\'t got the fabric I need. I\'m sure that with 10 Wabbit Fabrics, this dress will be my masterpiece!";
D.q[6001] = "It doesn\'t take a genius to understand. I almost forgot - this assembly is secret, so keep shtum, not a word...";
D.q[5435] = "";
D.q[1098] = "There are several types of powder but the most important part is knowing how to measure it out. For the militia, I make Nocabregor powder. It\'s cheap, stable and only requires a small bit of energy to go off. For fireworks, I use a powder with some saltpetre to avoid any needless risk. I also make mines which need a lot of sulphur. Anyway... I can\'t tell you much in a few minutes, it\'s a vast and complex science.";
D.q[5777] = "There are three main rules you must remember to play this game. First of all, the Gobball must not die! If one team kills a Gobball, no matter whether it\'s by accident or on purpose, the player\'s team will be disqualified. \nApart from that, nearly everything is allowed, but if you kill someone on the other team, you\'ll have to leave the game. Trainers and substitutes have places by the field and a maximum of five players per team can be on the field at any one time. You can however change places with a substitute. \nOh and by the way, anyone who\'s not on the field of play must keep out of the game!";
D.q[4134] = "There we go. The ship isn\'t quite in perfect shape yet, but we can still leave. According to the map, we\'ve not got far to go. If you want, you can wait on this island for a couple of days, and I\'ll come back and pick you up later...";
D.q[6429] = "There were several of them, Shere Hacanon was there I remember. He works at the south gate to the city, when he works at all.";
D.q[827] = "There is an enraged wolf roaming around the city in the front of Brakmar. Give it a thrashing... I hate those things... hope it never comes back...";
D.q[2817] = "There you go! Go back and make your offering right now, before all the bubbles pop!";
D.q[2355] = "There you go, I\'ve signed this little paper... It\'s official : you\'re an alchemist now. Should you have any questions, go back and ask Dragonsly.";
D.q[1262] = "There you go. Now go see your master.";
D.q[2019] = "There! Xelor\'s Sandglass is finished! This is my preferred medium for divination... Very well, let\'s have a look... *Kwartzwatch focuses on the flow of Epyss, then is overcome by bolts of lightning, and she drops the hourglass, which breaks* By the Twelve! What was that vision? Let me come back to my senses. May Xelor have mercy, I fear the worst...";
D.q[4541] = "These cursed Brakmarians will see that we can defend ourselves... and attack too! Speak to the commandant about the assault.";
D.q[1146] = "These cloaks are terrible... I hope it won\'t upset my men. You have every reason to be worried #1... Yuukk Yukk!";
D.q[2350] = "There\'s some pretty big monsters over there... Even my granddaddy never heard of them, they\'d scare a lop they would! And then there\'s all those old legends.";
D.q[4332] = "They sent YOU? I thought something was fishy. Well, what interesting exchange was that letter on about?";
D.q[5377] = "They ended up catching me. But before they did, I got some important details. Bad news for Brakmar I\'m afraid. A chief centaur Nilevaj I believe, got his hands on a powerful artefact. This object is so powerful that it could be used against Brakmar by a protector!";
D.q[3703] = "They attack those who desecrate Nature. This Elm is the last one in Incarnam. No one can cut this tree without suffering Sadida\'s wrath, and I fear that in his wrath he\'d destroy all Incarnam. That\'s why my magic keeps the lumberjacks away.";
D.q[6088] = "This Assembly is revealing more about certain people than I thought it would. It\'s always good to find out what your enemies are really like... and your friends.";
